text.tspan: Every year,
5 independant exchange periods
from 1 hour to 1 day per week
of work in class
The French children, together with their
teachers, decide on topics and make
reports on themes such as their school,
food, games, dance...
These reports can be made with videos,
soundtracks, texts, maps, quizzes or any
other media.
While the teachers accompany the pupils
in France, I intervene abroad with Par Le
Monde mediators to help the children
make reports to send to the French pupils.
We have tested your
recipes, Yum !!
But we had to replace the
semolina by a different
ingredient!
This is what we eat for breakfast :
Maroccan pancakes (Msemmens),
"mille trous" pancakes (Baghir),
semolina flatbread (Haracha).
What do you eat in France ?
